DescriptionText.En: "Light 'em up!"
"Ooooh, burn."
"Let's just stop and think about this."
"Hard to believe there were fields here once, and forests, and cities. I'm not too sure what's left to fight for now."

NameText.En: As captain, win 3 matches with no more than 1 death in Anglean

DescriptionText.En: "The hours pass cold and slow when you're not fighting to live."

NameText.En: Play 3 matches with at least 5 kills in Anglean

DescriptionText.En: "They'll take everything you have if you let them. Close your eyes for just a moment, and you'll open them naked."

NameText.En: Play 3 matches with no more than 1 death in Anglean

DescriptionText.En: "I prefer to conduct war in a gentlemanly fashion — from as far away as possible."

NameText.En: As captain, spot 20 ships at a distance of greater than 1500m (crew)
On helm, destroy 10 ships at a distance of at least 1000m (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "What are the chances?"

NameText.En: Spot 10 ships at a distance of greater than 1500m
Destroy 5 ships at a distance of greater than 800m

DescriptionText.En: "Trouble's on the horizon. Well, trouble's everywhere, but there's a bit of it right over there."

NameText.En: Spot 10 ships at a distance of greater than 1500m

DescriptionText.En: "The only bullets that count are the ones that hit."
"The engineer's task is to keep the ship flying long enough to shoot them more times than they shoot you."
"Try to learn from the mistakes of others. You won't live long enough to make all of them yourself."

NameText.En: Play 30 matches with any crewmate level 1-12

DescriptionText.En: "For a bit there, it almost looked like airship combat."

NameText.En: Play 30 matches with all crewmates level 1-12

DescriptionText.En: "Knowledge shared is knowledge increased."

NameText.En: Spend 30 minutes in Practice with any crewmate level 1-12

DescriptionText.En: "The combat airship exists solely to position and support the gunner, enabling him to fire on the enemy. If we fail to hit our targets, all is for naught."

NameText.En: Destroy 200 targets in Practice with any crewmates level 1-12 (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "You cannot propel yourself forward by patting yourself on the back."

NameText.En: Spend 30 minutes in Practice with pilots level 1-12 on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: "I swear they get younger every year."

NameText.En: Play 30 matches with any crewmates level 1-12

DescriptionText.En: "Good leaders have great advisors."
"No falcon flies but was first fledged."

NameText.En: Play 20 matches with any crewmates level 1-12

DescriptionText.En: "Enthusiasm rarely wins over skill, but it celebrates afterward anyway."

NameText.En: Capture 30 points with any crewmates level 1-12

DescriptionText.En: "Pass and you get to live!"

NameText.En: Destroy 50 ships with any crewmates level 1-12 (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "Experience is a hard teacher. First comes the test, then the lesson."
"What will they make of this world we've left them, I wonder?"

NameText.En: Play 30 matches with any crewmates level 1-12

DescriptionText.En: "I daresay I'm startin' to rub off on you some, eh? Oh, sorry, that's just a bit o' engine grease."
"Does as told, has a lively disposition, swings a wrench passing well, and don't get up to too much trouble."
"I've sailed on many a vessel in my time, and of all the captains I've ever had the pleasure of shipping under, I must say that you're the one who's standing here in front of me."
"Ye can tell a lot by th' company a fellow keeps — and by 'o keeps company with 'im."
"Seems popular with the lads, at any rate."
"Someday one of these young guns is going to shoot the likes of us out of the sky, mark my words. The best we can do is show them how to aim."
"So tell us, how's the view from up there, hey?"
"I'm telling you, they will be singing songs about us when we are gone!"
"When you've reached the top, there's nowhere to go but up! Isn't that so?"
"The only thing worse than not knowing is knowing and not telling."

NameText.En: Have completed "Career Shadowing" achievement in Teaching category

DescriptionText.En: "There's none I'd rather go to war with than these."
"An airship alone is like a bird without her flock, a fish without her school."
"With enemies like these, who needs friends?"
"War is such a dreadful business. The least we can do is be sporting about it."
"I've a few tricks left to play."
"There are times when one is called upon to perform the most difficult maneuvers merely to remain in one place."
"Don't talk to me about military MIGHT...it's all about military WILL!"
"M'favorite part was when th' ships fell down."
"Tell me where it hurts."
"You never know what you'll find when you venture out there. Usually unfriendly ships with guns pointed at you, but the point is, you never know."
"Aww, chute."
"Get ready, I'm gonna bring us in close. Real close."
"Strike true, and hold fast!"
"These grounder primitives don't understand anything that's not bright lights an' big explosions. You got to show 'em a little flash, make 'em respect your superior armaments."
"It's all about efficiency, optimization, and attention to the smallest detail."

NameText.En: Fully repair 50 engines less than 5 seconds after receiving damage

DescriptionText.En: "Recipe comes from a certain accomplished chemist of my acquaintance back in Anthos. 'Course, owing to the difficulty of obtaining supplies, I've had to make a few substitutions..."

NameText.En: Extinguish 70 fires on hull with Chemical Spray

DescriptionText.En: "We've got a lively one!"
"Standby for all hell breaking loose."

NameText.En: As captain, fully repair 100 engines less than 5 seconds after receiving damage (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "If I look like a parts factory exploded, well, that's because it very nearly did."
"Yes, I've given it a name, and no, I'm not sharing it with you."
"It eats, it breathes, it seeks to reproduce itself, and above all survive...is a fire not very like a man?"
"Technology is a wondrous thing. It continually provides us with new and better ways to shoot more and more things from ever farther away."
"No one dies today. Well, no one on our side."

Win 3 DMs with a perfect score against enemy captains all level 8+

DescriptionText.En: "I like the days when nothing blows up."

Win 3 DMs with a perfect score against enemy captains all level 8+

NameText.En: Win 30 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "I'm nae sure who's got who."

DescriptionText.En: "Ye gods, what a mess!"

NameText.En: Help a crewmate rebuild 30 non-gun parts

DescriptionText.En: "Too many cooks spoil the broth, but the dishes get done a lot quicker."

NameText.En: Help a crewmate rebuild 50 hull armor

DescriptionText.En: "We've got to get them before they get us."
"Ever hear tell o' the Beast o' th' Burren? Ships go missing 'twixt here an' Paritus, that's th' Beast swallowed 'em up..."

NameText.En: On helm, destroy 10 ships while unspotted in CP (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "D'ye know what they call an airship captain who's been through as many campaigns as I have? Alive ... 'cause that's the most remarkable thing about 'im."
"Shoulda' watched where you weren't goin'."

NameText.En: Destroy 60 parts while unspotted in CP

DescriptionText.En: "What more reason d'ye need?"
"A brief respite would certainly be to our advantage."

NameText.En: Rebuild 100 parts while unspotted in CP

DescriptionText.En: "When I said I'd follow you into battle and give you my undying loyalty, I honestly didn't expect it to last this long."
"We control the mountains, we control the passes. From this vantage point, we control the sky."

NameText.En: On helm, destroy 15 balloons with Spire (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "We didn't light it, but we didn't fight it, neither."
"Gunner name o' Blind Ike, demon in the clouds, I swear he found his mark better with a rag tied o'er his eyes. He sure didn't see that gap in the railing, though. R.I.P., Ike."

NameText.En: Destroy 20 parts on an unspotted ship inside a cloud

DescriptionText.En: "Not the fastest way to victory, but a satisfying one."
"D'you have anyone back home, watching the skies and waiting for you? Because I do."
"You know, it's quite difficult to work in these conditions."
"I hope this won't turn out like your last one. It took two months in skydock just to get the hull patched up."

NameText.En: Win 8 matches in Canyon Ambush (any size).
As captain, destroy 15 ships with Spire (crew) in Canyon Ambush (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "I have to admit a certain fondness for battered, broken things past their prime."

NameText.En: As captain, capture 20 points in Scrap

DescriptionText.En: "Quickest way to disarm a trap's to spring it."

NameText.En: Win 8 matches in Canyon Ambush (any size).
Destroy 15 ships with Charged Rounds in Canyon Ambush (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "I can't believe we're fighting over this."

NameText.En: Play 3 matches with 4 more kills than deaths in Scrap

DescriptionText.En: "I've felt safer walking down a Dragontown back alley at midnight. Back from the purser. Alone. And drunk."

NameText.En: Win 8 matches in Canyon Ambush (any size).
Fully repair 50 hull armor in Canyon Ambush (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "All the really good junk has already been taken."

NameText.En: Play 3 matches with 4 more kills than deaths in Scrap

DescriptionText.En: "Sacrifice is hard. It takes real thought, and courage, and will to act. Surviving's easy, it's just what comes natural."

NameText.En: Win 10 matches with no deaths against enemy captains all level 8+

DescriptionText.En: "What they don't know can't hurt us."

NameText.En: As captain, spot 60 ships while unspotted (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "I'd a mind ta paint some flames on th' sides, make it look more fearsome, but Chief said it'd just look t'be on fire."
"I almost wish I was closer so I could see the looks on their faces."

NameText.En: Spot 20 ships at a distance of greater than 2000m
Destroy 40 parts at a distance of greater than 1000m

DescriptionText.En: "Whoever builds the airship that flies twice as high as the rest will rule the world."
"Put them on the map, then wipe them off of it."

NameText.En: Spot 20 ships at a distance of greater than 2000m

DescriptionText.En: "I can make this ship do things yeh never even knew she were capable of."
"We are looking for some part of the world we haven't yet despoiled. Perhaps no airship built can fly that far."
"It's like my old sergeant always said, never bring a gun to a firefight! Tho' now I think about it, he said a lot of dreck tha' didn't make much sense..."
"Y'know, circle of life and all that guff. The short of it is, stuff just needs blowing up."
"A minor setback, one which I am confident we will overcome."
"I would rather perish among the clouds than live grubbing in the dirt."
"Sometimes gravity needs a little extra help."
"Curiously, my flight instructor omitted these maneuvers from the curriculum."
"He don't do much by halves, do he?"
"Any gambler'll tell ye, ye get a shot, ye take it."

NameText.En: Destroy 75 hull armor with Lesmok Rounds

DescriptionText.En: "Got to remember the three levels of priority: Urgent, Emergency, and Incoherent Screaming."

NameText.En: Extinguish 60 fires on balloon with Extinguisher
Rebuild 45 parts less than 5 seconds after destruction

DescriptionText.En: "It's my understanding that one typically seeks shelter FROM a storm, not IN it."

NameText.En: Fully repair 25 parts while in a hazardous cloud

DescriptionText.En: "Bird. Bird. Bird. Bird. Bird. Bird. ...Oh! Ship! SHIII—oops, no, no, sorry, false alarm. It's a bird."
"Fires are like little children. They get into everything, and they grow up too fast."

NameText.En: As captain, extinguish 50 fires less than 5 seconds after igniting (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "When you put it that way, we can't fail."

NameText.En: Help a crewmate rebuild 30 hull armor

DescriptionText.En: "There's a lot more deck-scrubbing than they tell you at the recruitment hall, that's for sure."
"Do you always yell out the name of fruits at moments of hightened tension?"
"Mastery of fire was humanity's first, greatest technological feat. Now look at us."
"Anyone would think we were returning from a pleasure cruise down the Abermar Valley, not a war. I hear Black Lake is lovely this time of year."

NameText.En: Win 30 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+
Win 3 matches with no deaths and at least 50% hull health against enemy captains all level 8+

DescriptionText.En: "It's important to have something to work towards."

NameText.En: Win 30 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "They should give out prizes for this kind of skill."

NameText.En: Win 30 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+
Win 3 matches with at least 5 kills against enemy captains all level 8+

DescriptionText.En: "Brings a tear to me eye."

NameText.En: Win 30 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "The only lasting damage was to me nerves."

NameText.En: Win 30 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+
Win 3 matches with no deaths and at least 50% hull health against enemy captains all level 8+

DescriptionText.En: "Ye gods, this is hard work."

NameText.En: Win 30 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "I would offer to show you how it's done, but that will prove impossible since you'll never even see me coming."

NameText.En: As captain, destroy 30 ships while unspotted (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "The wind is our pilot, the cliffs our gunners."
"It's almost insultin', them ignorin' us like this. My feelin's are a little hurt."
"It'll take mor'n we've got ta put all this back together."
"Let's not take the chance."
"I've only got three hands, y'know!"
"I would call for a moment to remember our fallen comrades, but I fear it will take more than the scant time that we have to recall them all."
"By the time you see us, it's too late. Your ship is mine."

NameText.En: Destroy 75 parts while unspotted in DM (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "We're here, and so are they. That's what you call an 'untenable position.'"
"What are you going to throw at us now, hey? Insults?"
"Were we stronger, faster, smarter, braver? Simply lucky? Beloved by the gods? Or despised by them?"
"It's a particularly effective form of diplomacy."
"Borders are to me as smoke in the breeze."

NameText.En: On helm, capture 30 points with Squid

DescriptionText.En: "No one owns the air. You've a right to just as much as you can suck down your lungs, and no more."
"I am a rock in the storm."
"Still got all yer fingers? So ye can count to five, right?"
"I'm going to focus on not blowing up, good luck with everything else."

NameText.En: Rebuild 35 balloons less than 10 seconds after destruction
Fully repair 35 hull armor less than 5 seconds after receiving damage

DescriptionText.En: "Perhaps the captain would enjoy smoking his pipe on the weather deck rather than in the hold with the fuel storage containers in future."

NameText.En: Extinguish 75 fires less than 10 seconds after igniting

DescriptionText.En: "Soon enough snow will fall and cover the wreckage, and there will be no trace we were ever here."

NameText.En: Win 10 matches in Fight Over Firnfeld.
Play 3 matches in Fight Over Firnfeld vs. captains lvl 8+ w/ 2 more kills than deaths.

DescriptionText.En: "It's just a bunch o' rocks, but it's our bunch o' rocks."

NameText.En: As captain, capture 10 points with Junker in Flayed

DescriptionText.En: "If we finish them off from close enough, maybe we can salvage some kindling for a fire and ruddy well warm ourselves up!"

NameText.En: Win 10 matches in Fight over Firnfeld (any size).
Destroy 3 ships (with guns) at a distance of less than 75m in Fight over Firnfeld (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "Shoot first. I forget how the rest of it goes."
"I would smile to express my relief at surviving, but I think my face is frozen."

NameText.En: Win 10 matches in Fight over Firnfeld (any size).
Win 3 perfect victories in Fight over Firnfeld (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "Out here we need our defenses more than ever."

NameText.En: Fully repair 25 hull armor in Flayed

DescriptionText.En: "It's not always about being the biggest, or the strongest, or the fastest. Sometimes it's just about being able to take the most hits and stay in the fight."

NameText.En: Win 30 matches with no deaths against enemy captains all level 8+
As captain, rebuild 30 parts less than 10 seconds after destruction (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "Beyond the horizon is the land of shadows, from which everything terrible and evil comes. Never take your eye off the horizon."

NameText.En: Spot 50 ships at a distance of greater than 1000m while unspotted (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "I've watched you wrench-swingers loads of times, I think I know how it's done. Not much to it, really."

NameText.En: Fully repair 150 guns less than 5 seconds after receiving damage

DescriptionText.En: "Nowt to do but watch birds."

NameText.En: Spot 25 ships at a distance of greater than 1000m

DescriptionText.En: "That's nothing. Back in Gato we used to race go-carts we built out of old war tanks. Won first place three years running, til my rig exploded."
"Curlews, storm brews; pair of swallows, fortune follows; raven at night, flee the fight; ship in the sky, battle's nigh!"

NameText.En: Spot 25 ships at a distance of greater than 1000m

DescriptionText.En: "You cannot garden in a battlefield. Blood is poor water for flowers, and grows only thorns."
"Let's see what's out there."
"I haven't known many gunners who could make a shot like that, and I've shot down half of 'em."
"One can hardly quibble with something so skillfully done."
"As ready as she'll ever be, Cap'n."
"I've a reputation to uphold."
"Ye can only plan as far out as yer guns can shoot."

NameText.En: On helm, destroy 25 ships at a distance of greater than 1000m (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "Our ancestors were giants. Their crowns grazed the heavens, and still they cried out for more room to grow. Yet we do not stand on their shoulders, but crunch their bones underfoot."
"It's a little light show we do to entertain the locals."
"They say fire was a gift from the gods. Only fair we should share it."

NameText.En: Set 125 parts on fire with Flares

DescriptionText.En: "Your 'emergency' ranks somewhere below the ship blowing up, fire on the portside engine, forgetting if I watered the captain's orange tree, and this hangnail on my thumb."

NameText.En: Extinguish 125 fires less than 10 seconds after igniting
Fully repair 125 parts less than 10 seconds after receiving damage

DescriptionText.En: "And ready for anything."
"Two horses pulling together cover more distance than four horses pulling apart."

NameText.En: As captain, help a crewmate rebuild 50 hull armor (crew)
As captain, fully repair 50 hull armor less than 5 seconds after receiving damage (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "Rise or fall, we go together."
"This probably isn't good."
"When it works, it works."
"It's all a grand game, isn't it?"

NameText.En: Destroy 25 ships at a distance of at least 1000m

DescriptionText.En: "The cause is just, and the principles are sound."
"Three simple rules: No grog on yer watch. They hit you, you hit them back harder. And I mean it about the grog."

NameText.En: Win 40 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+
Win 5 matches with 5 more kills than deaths against enemy captains all level 8+

DescriptionText.En: "Honor is a currency that once earned, can never be spent. Well, it's not accepted as widely as it used to be."

NameText.En: Win 50 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "I hit you, you hit me, I blew yer ship to smithereens. Who's to say who's the villain here?"

NameText.En: Win 40 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+
Win 5 matches with 5 more kills than deaths against enemy captains all level 8+

DescriptionText.En: "It don't make much difference to me whether or not we win, so long as they lose."

NameText.En: Win 50 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "They say for everything you do, some blighter does it to you three times as hard, and calls that balance."

NameText.En: Win 40 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+
Win 5 matches with 5 more kills than deaths against enemy captains all level 8+

DescriptionText.En: "Hard-fought, and well earned."

NameText.En: Win 50 matches against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "Ground's rising up, / And I don't know why / I'm caught between the devil / And the clear blue sky."
"That's the secret."

NameText.En: Win 10 matches with at least 5 kills against at least one enemy captain level 16+
Win 10 matches with no deaths against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "Sure, regular ammo has its uses. Makes great ballast."
"It's nae fair! They was workin' together!"

NameText.En: Win 20 matches with at least 5 kills against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "Just what this world needs, more weapons."
"Serve on a crew with someone for so long, and at the end you're either mates or mortal enemies. Mates is easier."

NameText.En: Win 20 matches with no deaths against at least one enemy captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "How d'ye win a race? Sure, ye can try t'be fastest. Or ye can cripple yer opponent, an' jes' walk t' th' finish. So, will ye race wi' me, laddie?"

NameText.En: Damage 75 parts with Tar Barrel in CP

DescriptionText.En: "We all make our mark on the world. Mostly scars."
"They say old gunners go deaf from all the noise o' gunfire an' whatnot. I wouldn't know, I never met a gunner who got to get old."
"Long the glories / And short the years / For them what make of war / Careers."
"If that doesn't get your turbines spinning, I don't know what will."
"When I'm done patchin' up ships and gettin' shot at, think I'll retire somewhere nice an' peaceful. A beach shack on the Storm Islands, mebbe, or a wee tent on the Nalm—Sylka border."
"Floats like a body in the salt sea."
"There's victory snatched from the jaws of defeat, and then there's honey lollies tugged from the lips of a small, sickly, idiot child. This, friends, is honey lollies for everyone."

NameText.En: Win 10 matches with no deaths & 100% hull health vs. at least one captain level 16+

DescriptionText.En: "Let me at 'em!"

NameText.En: Destroy 20 ships at a distance of less than 100m

DescriptionText.En: "Were they aiming for us, or giving us an artillery salute?"

NameText.En: Win 10 matches with no deaths & 100% hull health vs. at least 1 captain lvl 16+

DescriptionText.En: "I'm giving you all she's got and quite a bit more. I would calculate the efficiency rating more precisely, but my arm's about to fall off."

NameText.En: Fully repair 125 engines less than 5 seconds after receiving damage

DescriptionText.En: "She looks as good as new! Or at least as good as the day we stole her off the Dragontown dock and gave her hull a fresh repaint to confuse the Imperial authorities."

NameText.En: Win 10 matches with no deaths & 100% hull health vs. at least 1 captain lvl 16+

DescriptionText.En: "Looking backward we learn not only what we're capable of accomplishing, but how not to go about it."

NameText.En: As captain, destroy 20 ships with Goldfish in Paritan 2v2 or 3v3.

DescriptionText.En: "One way or another, we all wind up back here."

NameText.En: Win 20 matches in Battle on the Dunes (any size).
Get 5 perfect wins in Battle on the Dunes (any size) vs. at least one captain lvl 16+

DescriptionText.En: "People used to live in this mess?"
"They hit us, we hit them, so they hit us. On it goes."

NameText.En: Win 20 matches in Battle on the Dunes (any size).
Destroy 50 balloons in Battle on the Dunes (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "They built towers so high that any grounder could get above the clouds just by taking the stairs."

NameText.En: Fully repair 50 engines in Paritan 2v2 or 3v3.

DescriptionText.En: "Every battle is the decisive one, the final push, the one that ends the war. Has to be. There's a new war starting tomorrow."

NameText.En: Play 5 matches w/ 0 deaths & at least 50% hull health in Dunes vs. at least 1 captain lvl 16+

DescriptionText.En: "Sometimes a ship just needs ta fly."
"They draw up and salute at my coming, for they think their wanderings are at an end."
"Like shooting ticks in a thimble."

NameText.En: Destroy 125 parts from a distance of greater than 1300m

DescriptionText.En: "They flee when they see me coming, for they fear their lives are at an end."
"Sure, the world's going to hell in a handbasket, but damned if we don't have the nicest handbasket out there."
"They cheer to see me coming, for they hope their troubles are at an end."

NameText.En: Win 10 more matches as the Underdog.
Win 20 more matches as the Underdog.
Win 30 more matches as the Underdog.
Complete 5 more matches as the Underdog.
Complete 10 more matches as the Underdog.
Complete 20 more matches as the Underdog.
Win 40 more matches as the Underdog.

DescriptionText.En: Where's the fun without the risk?

NameText.En: Complete 10 more games with your captain as novice.

DescriptionText.En: Leadership will be assigned at random.

NameText.En: Complete 15 more games with your captain as novice.

DescriptionText.En: How can the enemy know what you're doing if your captain doesn't know what he's doing?

NameText.En: Complete 30 more games with your captain as novice.

DescriptionText.En: Dangerous for you is dangerous for them!

NameText.En: Complete 60 more games with your captain as novice.

DescriptionText.En: Luck and skill are interchangable after you win.

NameText.En: Win 10 more games with a novice as your captain.

DescriptionText.En: "Maybe we turn away from the firestorm."

NameText.En: Win 15 more games with a novice as your captain.

DescriptionText.En: Don't let the numbers fool you, we always had this in the bag.

NameText.En: Win 30 more games with a novice as your captain.

DescriptionText.En: Never underestimate the newbie.

NameText.En: Win 60 more games with a novice as your captain.

DescriptionText.En: Look even smarter by comparison!

NameText.En: Complete ten more games with one novice on your crew

DescriptionText.En: Partner in crime or meatshield?

NameText.En: Complete 25 more games with one novice on your crew

DescriptionText.En: High pitched screams can come from any throat.

NameText.En: Complete 30 more games with one novice on your crew
The Present and the Future Vet

DescriptionText.En: Visiting players with the ghost of games future.

NameText.En: Complete 100 more games with one novice on your crew

DescriptionText.En: Which one is the evil newbie?

NameText.En: Complete ten more games with two novices on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: Mistakes now in stereo!

NameText.En: Complete 25 more games with two novices on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: The stars say you'll need something for that headache.

NameText.En: Complete 30 more games with two novices on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: Both of you sit in different corners!

NameText.En: Complete 100 more games with two novices on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: Maybe you're right, but they're louder

NameText.En: Complete ten more games with three novices on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: Powered by chips and soda!

NameText.En: Complete 25 more games with three novices on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: No player is going to make you leave a battle.

NameText.En: Complete 30 more games with three novices on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: Sometimes its frustrating being the smartest person in the room.

NameText.En: Complete 100 more games with three novices on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: Even baby birds can dive bomb.

NameText.En: Win ten more games with one novice on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: I kill, you kill, I win, you win.

NameText.En: Win 20 more games with one novice on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: Showing off the dance of death.

NameText.En: Win 30 more games with one novice on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: Evening the odds doesn't always mean equal numbers.

NameText.En: Win 100 more games with one novice on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: Novice or not, those that stand with me will be my brother.

NameText.En: Win 10 more games with two novices on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: At the very least you can drop them on someone's head.

NameText.En: Win 20 more games with two novices on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: Winning hearts and minds by winning games.

NameText.En: Win 30 more games with two novices on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: The true master doesn't just avoid mistakes, he fixes them.

NameText.En: Win 100 more games with two novices on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: Being shown the wrong path makes the correct path a lot more obvious.

NameText.En: Win 10 more games with three novices on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: They're not actually that jolly, except for Roger.

NameText.En: Win 20 more games with three novices on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: Right out of hell and into the winner's circle.

NameText.En: Win 30 more games with three novices on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: Proving you're strong enough to carry three people and a ship.

NameText.En: Win 100 more games with three novices on your crew.

DescriptionText.En: Unfettered by the chains of mortality.

NameText.En: Win five more games with zero deaths and at least one novice on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: In possession of so much experience you are free to share it.

NameText.En: Win five more games with zero deaths and at least one novice on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: Complete command is complete victory.

NameText.En: Win ten more games with zero deaths and at least one novice on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: Who can call themselves an unbeliever when they realize they're a god?

NameText.En: Win 20 more games with zero deaths and at least one novice on your ship.

DescriptionText.En: Even the minnows are the size of killer whales.
Including Pastries, Knights, Armies and Death itself!
Never one to say no to a good fight
Was it ever in doubt that you'd end up in battle?
Even the legends hype their stories
Is it still arrogant if you're always right?
1000 cuts mean less than the final blow.
You don't get this far without leaving a few bodies behind.
Even the skies have their fair share.

NameText.En: Win 10 vet games with one or less deaths

DescriptionText.En: The Sirens Sing of You

NameText.En: Win 20 vet games with one or less deaths

DescriptionText.En: Welcome to the deep end of the ocean.

NameText.En: Complete ten more vet games as an underdog

DescriptionText.En: Your chance to see which title you deserve.

NameText.En: Complete 25 more vet games as an underdog

DescriptionText.En: Don't Panic

NameText.En: Complete 42 more vet games as an underdog

DescriptionText.En: Riding storms can be the greatest thrill.

NameText.En: Complete 100 vet games as an underdog

DescriptionText.En: Victory doesn't stay in one person's hands for long.

NameText.En: Win 10 more vet games as an underdog.

DescriptionText.En: Nothing more fun than screwing with the system.

NameText.En: Win 20 more vet games as an underdog.

DescriptionText.En: Never tell me the odds!

NameText.En: Win 30 more vet games as an underdog.

DescriptionText.En: Only possible to the truly brave, insanely lucky, or truly insane.

DescriptionText.En: "Remember to break ground and fly into the wind, not the other way around."
"You know which end the bullet comes out? And which bit you squeeze to make it happen? Then hop to, hotshot!"
"If it ain't broke, don't fix it; but if it is, then by all means, do."
"You never know what's hiding in those clouds. On a bad day, it's you."

NameText.En: On helm, spend 360 seconds inside a cloud

DescriptionText.En: "Hit as many things as you can, give their engies somethin' to do."
"FIRE ON THE HULL!"

NameText.En: Fully repair 5 hull armor with Mallet
Extinguish 3 fires on hull with Extinguisher

DescriptionText.En: "Firin' explosives while th' armor's up's like tryin'a stick yer spoon in a tin o' beans without openin' th' lid firs'."

NameText.En: As captain, destroy 10 hull armor with Gatling (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "Turns out they just like hitting things."
"Why should gunners get to have all the fun?"
"Don't let a little success go to your head. Wait for a lot of success."
"Nice shooting. True, half of it was at friendlies, but your aim was very good."
"By my count, I've rebuilt the entire ship three or four times over by now."
"Many hands make short work."
"Crisis averted. Now back to your stations!"
"Can they swing a wrench? Do they hit something half the time? They'll do."
"Position, position, position. Where are you...and where are they?"

NameText.En: As captain, spot 10 ships at a distance of at least 750m in DM (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "They called her the Whistler, on account of how her hull was full of holes. You could hear her coming a mile off."
"The weapons could use an upgrade, to be sure. I think some of this stuff dates back to the War."
"Her fins cut the breeze, armored scales glinting in the sun...her guns waved a salute as she dipped and glided toward us."

NameText.En: On helm, destroy 20 ships with Goldfish (crew)

DescriptionText.En: "On the ship of the blind, the one-eyed man is captain — and the gunner's a lousy shot."

NameText.En: Destroy 60 parts on an unspotted ship

DescriptionText.En: "Flying's just like swimming, except for the falling."
"Look at this place...this is the fate we've all so far escaped. And yet we keep coming back here, vultures circling our own bones."

NameText.En: Win 5 matches in Battle on the Dunes (any size).
Destroy 16 parts with ramming in Battle on the Dunes (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "We get in and take what we need, but I've no intention of adding our wrecked carcass to this slag heap. There's nothin' here worth dyin' for."

NameText.En: Win 5 matches in Battle on the Dunes (any size).
Destroy 35 guns in Battle on the Dunes (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "This stuff was mountains, once. Now it's a sea, and we're like to drown in it."

NameText.En: Win 6 matches in Battle on the Dunes (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "Get 'em in your sights and never let 'em go."
"I see them. Oh, I see them."

NameText.En: Spot 30 ships at a distance of at least 750m

DescriptionText.En: "Death is always in the corner of your eye."

NameText.En: Spot 30 ships at a distance of at least 750m

DescriptionText.En: "Move, shoot, repair, communicate. Everything follows from this."
"What matters in this world is not so much what ye've done, but who saw ye do it."

NameText.En: Shoot and destroy 3 non-firing targets in Practice
Shoot and destroy 3 armed targets in Practice

DescriptionText.En: "Nothing brightens my day more than a burst balloon."
"Reeling in good catches since the inagural flight of the Icarus."

NameText.En: Graduate from Novice (reach level 8 in Pilot, Gunner, or Engineer).

DescriptionText.En: "Never thought I'd find use for this little thing, but WOW."

NameText.En: Graduate from Novice (reach level 8 in Pilot, Gunner, or Engineer).

DescriptionText.En: "Bread and butter, least for now!"
"Nothing makes me cackle more than the face of a pilot after I burst his balloon."
"PUAHAHAHAHAAHAHA!"

NameText.En: Graduate from Novice (reach level 8 in Pilot, Gunner, or Engineer).

DescriptionText.En: "There was a time when I swore this had homing on it..."
"Making it rain, Age of Air style."
"Those marks on the side of the gun? Yeah, those are my kills."
"Pew pew pew!"
"I don't want to talk about it."
"First time I saw this, sweet mother of god!"
"There's not enough plaid on this."
"Come meet my... not so little friend?"

NameText.En: Graduate from Novice (reach level 8 in Pilot, Gunner, or Engineer).

DescriptionText.En: "I remember steering one of these when I was babe.  Ah, memories."
"Reminds me of my brother, dim looking but capable of holding its own."
"That drunk gunner at the pub one time gives new meaning to 'Jet like a Squid'"

NameText.En: Graduate from Novice (reach level 8 in Pilot, Gunner, or Engineer).

DescriptionText.En: "No matter which direction the wind blows, this boat stands still... unlike my hair."

NameText.En: Graduate from Novice (reach level 8 in Pilot, Gunner, or Engineer).

DescriptionText.En: "Spinning the ship round and round makes for a good party."

NameText.En: Graduate from Novice (reach level 8 in Pilot, Gunner, or Engineer).

DescriptionText.En: "It's just so... well, it's a good ramming ship."
"Scares me to think what my crew is doing in all those passage ways."

NameText.En: Graduate from Novice (reach level 8 in Pilot, Gunner, or Engineer).

DescriptionText.En: "Makes a tasty steak.  I love the burnt bits."
"A city with a name forgotten. Tragic."
"Beautiful landscapes, cacophony of mortar rounds."

NameText.En: Complete 30 matches on King of Flayed Hills

DescriptionText.En: "The brothers that never stop fighting."

NameText.En: Complete 30 matches on Battle on the Dunes (any size).

DescriptionText.En: "I pray my ship pilot steers vigilantly."

NameText.En: Complete 30 matches on Water Hazard 3v3 or Water Hazard 2v2.

DescriptionText.En: "The land will always draw some kind of attention."
"If only we could find the people who built these monsters."
"Some decide to fight on terms, but why do it at all?"

NameText.En: Complete 30 matches on Duel at Dawn.

DescriptionText.En: "The Yeshans are always nearby, keeping watch on their borders."

NameText.En: Complete 30 matches on Canyon Ambush 2v2 or 3v3.

DescriptionText.En: "Fjordlanders are indeed in a tough situation."

NameText.En: Complete 30 matches on Northern Fjords 2v2 or 3v3.

DescriptionText.En: "What comes out of the ground returns in a fiery rain."
"One of the few great industrial marvels still operational."

NameText.En: Complete 30 matches on Raid on the Refinery or Clash at Blackcliff 2v2/3v3.

DescriptionText.En: "Here, silence is a blessing."

NameText.En: Complete 30 matches on Fight over Firnfield.

DescriptionText.En: "No city truly ever sleeps, even one in ruins."
"So, you've crewed on a few ships and feel ready for the big league?  Get ready, you're in for a ride!"

NameText.En: Become a level 8 Gunner, Engineer, or Pilot to graduate from Novice.

DescriptionText.En: "I forgot where I left my mines.  Woops."

NameText.En: Graduate from Novice (reach level 8 in Pilot, Gunner, or Engineer).

DescriptionText.En: "In the Fjordland Royal Courts, I met this juggler... he was the best juggler I ever met."

Description.En: Maintaining ship components, making critical repairs, and putting out fires in the heat of battle, Engineers keep the ship flying when everything is falling apart.
Gunners operate the weaponry aboard an airship to neutralize threats, combining quick reflexes and sure aim with a thorough knowledge of all the tools of war.
Navigator, strategist, and commander, the Pilot flies the ship, scopes out the battlefield, chooses engagements, and keeps the crew working as a cohesive unit.
